00:38:30.490 --> 00:38:31.790
This first poem is called

00:38:31.790 --> 00:38:36.030
"He Got Me Flowers Today"
[inaudible] Tracy K. Smith;

00:38:36.030 --> 00:38:38.420
for Mama and Auntie Julie.

00:38:39.610 --> 00:38:42.840
"Birds stab greedy beaks
into trunk and seed,

00:38:42.840 --> 00:38:46.590
spill husk onto the heap where
my dreaming and loving live.

00:38:46.590 --> 00:38:48.890
Tracy K. Smith."

00:38:51.550 --> 00:38:55.050
"My fleeting body is
a vase of flowers,

00:38:55.050 --> 00:38:57.460
love is the brass knuckle.

00:38:57.460 --> 00:38:59.630
He tells me he loves me.

00:38:59.630 --> 00:39:01.350
He is sorry.

00:39:01.350 --> 00:39:03.240
He is dirty water.

00:39:03.240 --> 00:39:05.760
Regardless, I am still alive.

00:39:05.760 --> 00:39:09.610
I am still alive
on borrowed time,

00:39:09.610 --> 00:39:11.600
kitchen under the hot comb,

00:39:11.600 --> 00:39:15.270
my body a permed
attitude, a cracked vase.

00:39:15.270 --> 00:39:19.890
Love is the second home, a
plan B, a planned parenthood.

00:39:19.890 --> 00:39:21.560
My body is the vase.

00:39:21.560 --> 00:39:23.980
The vase is a casket for a rose,

00:39:23.980 --> 00:39:26.620
because even a dead
thing needs a home.

00:39:26.620 --> 00:39:31.020
Love is the rose handled thorn
first, the vase is my house,

00:39:31.020 --> 00:39:32.980
framed for my brief body.

00:39:32.980 --> 00:39:36.920
I make sure to leave room for
fist, their straining knuckles.

00:39:36.920 --> 00:39:41.370
My body pedals into a casket of
water, the water is a dirty man.

00:39:41.370 --> 00:39:43.310
The man is time I borrowed.

00:39:43.310 --> 00:39:46.290
My body is a rose,
fish out of water.

00:39:46.290 --> 00:39:48.410
Love is the alternative.

00:39:48.410 --> 00:39:51.260
But a living thing does
what it can to survive.

00:39:51.260 --> 00:39:54.110
My stem escaped and
ran away with a sink.

00:39:54.110 --> 00:39:58.510
A man tried to catch
me and drowned."

00:39:58.510 --> 00:40:02.700
[ Applause ]

00:40:02.700 --> 00:40:05.900
And then the second
poem is for my city,

00:40:05.900 --> 00:40:08.550
because people throw
dirt on Chicago so often

00:40:08.550 --> 00:40:11.090
that I feel we might
end up under it.

00:40:11.090 --> 00:40:13.290
It's after Jayne Cortez.

00:40:13.290 --> 00:40:18.050
"I am Windy City.

00:40:18.050 --> 00:40:21.590
Here is my tomato head baton
scattered badge in blue.

00:40:21.590 --> 00:40:25.350
I got my cousin's ears of corn
gentrifying in the melting pot,

00:40:25.350 --> 00:40:27.210
my mouth a mercury lake.

00:40:27.210 --> 00:40:29.130
I baptized John Baptiste
in a bonfire.

00:40:29.130 --> 00:40:33.620
I am Windy City of red
meat, stockyards of men

00:40:33.620 --> 00:40:37.360
in factories inside my belly,
a jungle of segregated joints.

00:40:37.360 --> 00:40:40.590
Rub my navy pores with the
blood of Betadine boys,

00:40:40.590 --> 00:40:42.500
making steel and stealing it.

00:40:42.500 --> 00:40:46.190
I am Windy -- [makes sounds]
making steel and stealing it."

00:40:46.190 --> 00:40:47.490
Sorry, you all.

00:40:47.490 --> 00:40:50.910
"I am Windy City of
Cabrini Green giants.

00:40:50.910 --> 00:40:53.960
Hear my Newport throat
croak an eight-hour workday,

00:40:53.960 --> 00:40:55.960
a Haymarket rally
in the projects,

00:40:55.960 --> 00:40:57.740
pipe bomb at Pullmans
Pied Piper.

00:40:57.740 --> 00:40:59.040
I work for no one.

00:40:59.040 --> 00:41:03.040
I am Windy City of bloody
gums, my teeth a collection

00:41:03.040 --> 00:41:05.140
of [inaudible] earrings,
which are kind

00:41:05.140 --> 00:41:07.870
of for the rest of
Gringo, Illinois.

00:41:07.870 --> 00:41:11.940
My boys cleanse the white city
with a storm of gunpowder tears.

00:41:11.940 --> 00:41:14.490
I am Windy City only dressed
in white on Valentines

00:41:14.490 --> 00:41:17.370
for all my lovers [inaudible]
at the hands of Chiraq,

00:41:17.370 --> 00:41:19.960
a man I don't know who
keeps trying to wife me.

00:41:19.960 --> 00:41:21.370
Chiraq is [inaudible]
peeping toms

00:41:21.370 --> 00:41:24.320
who have a license
to strip search.

00:41:24.320 --> 00:41:27.180
Chiraq turned churches
into resale gun stores.

00:41:27.180 --> 00:41:29.380
Chiraq attracts songs
[inaudible] sung

00:41:29.380 --> 00:41:32.950
into the wrong ear, Chiraq city
of lost, boys under the hood.

00:41:32.950 --> 00:41:36.440
Chiraq could never take my
face value of royal flush

00:41:36.440 --> 00:41:39.440
in Chicago River, my
Leaning Sears Tower of Pizza,

00:41:39.440 --> 00:41:42.490
my Heineken and soul food
[inaudible] tap dancing barefoot

00:41:42.490 --> 00:41:44.020
my hotheaded friends.

00:41:44.020 --> 00:41:48.390
My confetti flesh comrades,
come, break bread with me."

00:41:48.390 --> 00:41:50.190
Thank you.

