poetry is their faith.

00:49:35.990 --> 00:49:39.670
And for you, you have multiple
manifestations of how you,

00:49:39.670 --> 00:49:43.190
and how that intersects with
your story, your back story.

00:49:43.190 --> 00:49:46.580
So you want to shine a little
more light on that for us?

00:49:46.580 --> 00:49:48.950
&gt;&gt; Cassidy Martin: Sure,
I'm always happy to talk

00:49:48.950 --> 00:49:50.990
about God; you already know.

00:49:50.990 --> 00:49:56.700
So [laughter] when you love
from -- this is from personal --

00:49:56.700 --> 00:49:59.000
I know we're in a government
place, I don't care, but,

00:49:59.000 --> 00:50:03.000
you know, from a personal
-- when you love God,

00:50:03.000 --> 00:50:05.930
you see Him in everything
you do.

00:50:05.930 --> 00:50:10.410
And it's -- but my
take on poetry and God,

00:50:10.410 --> 00:50:13.910
the way they interweave doesn't
just come from me saying, "Oh,

00:50:13.910 --> 00:50:15.420
I love God," then,
"I love poetry."

00:50:15.420 --> 00:50:19.120
I kind of feel like poetry
has the spirit of Him.

00:50:19.120 --> 00:50:21.180
It's welcoming, it's loving,

00:50:21.180 --> 00:50:23.680
it's expression,
it's caring for.

00:50:23.680 --> 00:50:28.200
Like my mentors, I will
say they're godsend

00:50:28.200 --> 00:50:31.600
because they take care of me;
they feed me, they clothe me,

00:50:31.600 --> 00:50:34.340
they take me to birthday
parties and weddings and stuff.

00:50:34.340 --> 00:50:36.900
So it's like everything
that's come

00:50:36.900 --> 00:50:41.120
out of poetry have been
opportunities, have been family,

00:50:41.120 --> 00:50:45.430
and I feel like that is
the channel that God put me

00:50:45.430 --> 00:50:49.020
through to be able to
speak through poetry.

00:50:49.020 --> 00:50:52.860
And then by doing that, I
feel like I speak for Him.

00:50:52.860 --> 00:50:58.000
I speak for not just my
god, but a greater purpose,

00:50:58.000 --> 00:50:59.830
which is something that
everyone can relate to,

00:50:59.830 --> 00:51:01.740
whether they are
religious or not.

00:51:01.740 --> 00:51:04.270
So I feel like every
one of us up here,

00:51:04.270 --> 00:51:06.580
whether we have the
same religion or not,

00:51:06.580 --> 00:51:10.810
we have a message, and poetry is
how we get that message across.

00:51:10.810 --> 00:51:13.890
And I'm thankful for
God for everything.

00:51:13.890 --> 00:51:16.620
But the opportunities
that He's given me

00:51:16.620 --> 00:51:22.150
through poetry have just been
the apex of my entire life.

00:51:22.150 --> 00:51:25.890
And to be honest -- well
a lot of teachers say --

00:51:25.890 --> 00:51:27.320
I will say one thing,
a lot of teachers say

00:51:27.320 --> 00:51:30.150
that if they can reach
one student per year,

00:51:30.150 --> 00:51:31.450
then their job is --

00:51:31.450 --> 00:51:33.630
then they've reached their
goal, that's their job.

00:51:33.630 --> 00:51:37.120
Well, for me, was one person.

00:51:37.120 --> 00:51:39.600
It was [inaudible] I
